{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-blog-wp-post-slug-js","path":"/blog/building-my-portfolio-site-and-blog/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"featuredImage":{"node":{"altText":"","sourceUrl":"https://lucashubbard.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/project-thumbnail.jpg"}},"date":"March 11th, 2022","title":"Building My Portfolio Site and Blog","content":"\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p>My WordPress blog just wasn&#8217;t cutting it.  As far as WordPress blogs go, there was nothing wrong with it. I had a portfolio page for my video work and photography. I enjoyed formatting and managing my blog posts with WordPress. It was a fine WordPress blog, but I&#8217;m a front end web developer. A personal site built with a WordPress theme just felt a little amateurish.  It was time for a redesign.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Designing The Site</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In search of inspiration, I scoured Behance for designs that stood out to me. I noticed that many of the designs included extra information, such as font and color descriptions. I could see how this extra information and attractive formatting helped communicate the overall feel of the design. I was excited to put together a design that felt like a product in itself, I also figured it would make for good practice. <a href=\"https://www.behance.net/gallery/139210511/Lucas-Hubbard-Portfolio-and-Blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" title=\"You can find by final design on Behance\">You can find by final design on Behance</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>I wanted to create a site that brought to mind conifer forests and rivers brimming with glacial melt. I was inspired by photos I had taken at Glacier National park couple of years prior. I chose my topography with the parks early 20<sup>th</sup> century lodge in mind. I was going for something classy, rustic, and timeless. I selected my fonts from Google fonts and used Adobe Kuler to create my color scheme. The design work was done in Photoshop.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-2798 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\" data-reactroot=\"\"><div style=\"max-width:1024px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg height=&#x27;576&#x27; width=&#x27;1024&#x27; xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27; version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"1\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" data-src=\"/_gatsby/image/6c32f427083bb90d7138d84c2a6977a0/2e45081cb07f0df31004154cf1e22444/font-color-info.jpg?u=https%3A%2F%2Flucashubbard.com%2Fwordpress%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Ffont-color-info.jpg&amp;a=w%3D256%26h%3D144%26fm%3Djpg%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2022-03-11T14%3A48%3A56\" data-srcset=\"/_gatsby/image/6c32f427083bb90d7138d84c2a6977a0/2e45081cb07f0df31004154cf1e22444/font-color-info.jpg?u=https%3A%2F%2Flucashubbard.com%2Fwordpress%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Ffont-color-info.jpg&amp;a=w%3D256%26h%3D144%26fm%3Djpg%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2022-03-11T14%3A48%3A56 256w,/_gatsby/image/6c32f427083bb90d7138d84c2a6977a0/96b647ec7d907c05daf79ebbaf49d64f/font-color-info.jpg?u=https%3A%2F%2Flucashubbard.com%2Fwordpress%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2Ffont-color-info.jpg&amp;a=w%3D512%26h%3D288%26fm%3Djpg%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2022-03-11T14%3A48%3A56 512w,/_gatsby/image/6c32f427083bb90d7138d84c2a6977a0/445de7002b86e33254a5db750f4f2f35/font-color-info.